messages.message:
Patch Set 1:

I'm aware the new "city" must be added to each localisation, lest the app crash on any other locale than en_GB; however, I expected that there is a better way to do that than edit each and every res/values-*/array.xml by hand. I'm not familiar with the localisation system used here, but on the ones I have used in the past, there is a command to automatically add the new strings to all localisations, marking them as "not yet translated", and translators can afterwards go through untranslated strings. So how do I do that with this "android resources"-based system? I didn't easily find it in an Internet search.

Also, I didn't know what value to put in msgid; it looks like an automatically generated and/or random value. I expect the same command that updates all translations also inserts the right msgid.
